======================================================================
Part 5: INTERIOR VERTEX — Structural diversity
======================================================================

For source v: δ(relative cycle) is a BALANCED flow on ALL arcs of T\v
  = a 1-cycle in T\v
  Question: do these specific balanced flows always lie in B₁?
  Answer: YES at n=5 (verified). Why?

For interior v: δ(relative cycle) is a SIGNED mix from 3 position types
  = more diverse, harder to be a pure cycle
  The key structural difference makes δ injective.

